text.tspan: God in Christ drew me—Sweet is the story
Life of compassion, kind words and gestures,
God’s love revealed in His human ways,
Feasting with sinners, healing the lepers,
How deep His pity, mercy and grace!
Christ was uplifted, draws all men to Him:
The cross of Christ—O fathomless love!
By men afflicted, by God forsaken,
There He redeemed us by His shed blood.
All of death’s forces could not subdue Him;
Seed of the Woman, Satan He trod,
Broke all our bondage, raised us up with Him,
Made us alive, brought us into God.
Lord, Christ, and Leader, Savior of all!
This our confession, Christ is our Savior,
Our God has raised Him on the third day,
His love transforms us for His good pleasure,
Builds us up into His dwelling place.
